A '''paleolith''' or ''palaeolith'' is an archaic word for a stone relic of the [[Paleolithic]] [[era]]. "Palæolith: a rude stone implement or object of the earlier stone age".<ref>Davidson, T. (1901) ''Chambers's Twentieth Century Dictionary of the English Language''. London: W. & R. Chambers; p. 651</ref>

